Title "Cyclic Groups"

Introduction
"
A group is **cyclic** if some single element generates the entire
group ‚Äî that is, every element can be written as an integer power
of the generator.

In Lean, this is the typeclass `IsCyclic G`. The characterization
in terms of `zpowers` is:

`isCyclic_iff_exists_zpowers_eq_top : IsCyclic G ‚Üî ‚àÉ g, zpowers g = ‚ä§`

A group is cyclic if and only if there exists an element whose
zpowers subgroup is the whole group.

Given that `zpowers g = ‚ä§` (i.e., `g` generates the whole group),
prove `IsCyclic G`.
"

